entries.title: Mongolia trying to 'diversify' gas sector to get away from dependence on Russian neighbour
entries.description: The deputy prime minister of Mongolia has defended his country buying almost 100% of its gas from Russia, saying that its position as a large landlocked country presents "a lot of problems and issues".

entries.title: Protests in Peru leave 'thousands of tourists stranded' in gateway city to Machu Picchu
entries.description: Thousands of tourists have reportedly been left stranded in the Peruvian city of Cusco along with hundreds of others in the area around the Inca citadel of Machu Picchu because of anti-government protests.

entries.title: Family pay tribute to 'beautiful soul' killed in incident on Qatari oil rig
entries.description: The family of a British man who died after a "non-work related incident" involving three Britons aboard an oil rig in Qatar have paid tribute to "an amazing, one-of-a-kind, beautiful soul".

entries.title: Migrants rescued from second boat on same night four lives lost in Channel
entries.description: Fifty people were rescued after a second boat containing migrants started sinking on the same night four people died in a separate incident in the English Channel.

entries.title: Gianni Infantino secures backing to potentially extend FIFA presidency until 2031
entries.description: Gianni Infantino has secured backing from the FIFA Council to potentially extend his presidency until 2031 - beyond the 12-year limit envisaged in reforms of the scandal-plagued football body he helped to draw up.

entries.title: 'So good to be home': Brittney Griner leaves medical centre and plans WNBA return
entries.description: US basketball star Brittney Griner has been released from a medical centre in Texas and made her first public comments following her release from a Russian penal colony.

entries.title: Lionel Messi in numbers: After 791 goals and seven Ballon d'Or awards - one win could cement his spot as the world's greatest footballer
entries.description: With an astonishing 791 goals for club and country, 41 team trophies and a record seven Ballon d'Ors to his name, Lionel Messi has already secured his status as a true footballing great.

entries.title: Ukraine 'preparing' for Russia to invade from north, top commander says
entries.description: Ukraine is preparing for Russia to try again to invade from the north - maybe around the anniversary of its first, failed attempt to seize Kyiv last February, a top commander has said.

entries.title: Life finds a way: How climate change helped dinosaur success story
entries.description: Climate change played a key role in the ascendancy of the earliest dinosaurs, according to new research.

entries.title: Toddler survives being swallowed by a hippo
entries.description: A two-year-old boy has survived being swallowed by a hippo in Uganda.

entries.title: Few bombshells expected as JFK assassination archives released
entries.description: The release of thousands of documents relating to the assassination of John F Kennedy is unlikely to give any major revelations over the shooting of the US president in 1963.

entries.title: Three children among 18 killed in Malaysian landslide as rescuers dig for missing
entries.description: At least 18 people have been killed, with another 15 feared buried under mud, in a landslide at a Malaysian tourist campsite.

entries.title: Giant aquarium home to 1,500 fish bursts at Berlin hotel
entries.description: A massive aquarium has burst in Berlin, spilling one million litres of water and 1,500 tropical fish on to the lobby of a hotel and nearby streets.

entries.title: Russia launches 'massive missile attack' on Ukraine
entries.description: Russia has launched a "massive missile attack" on Ukraine, officials said, knocking out power and forcing people to take cover in shelters across the country.

entries.title: Ten dead, including five children, in France fire
entries.description: Ten people, including five children aged between three and 15 years old, have been killed in a fire near the French city of Lyon.

entries.title: Failed landing sees pilot eject as military jet nosedives onto runway in Texas
entries.description: A pilot safely ejected from a military jet after a failed landing that was caught on video in North Texas.
